{"TopicId":107260,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Sonic booms","CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T19:45:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T19:45:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat it says on the tin. Come on, add sonic boom effects when a ship breaks the sound barrier \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"r4pt0r","CreatedById":90471,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T19:46:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ewhat do you mean effects? like sound, a loud bang of some sort?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T19:55:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIn theory I\u0027d like this. It would need to be really nicely implemented though, it could end up being a rather buggy sound effect. ie what happens if you\u0027re flying just around the threshold for it, that may result in the sound constantly being played which would be rather unpleasant.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T20:14:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022r4pt0r\u0022 data-cite=\u0022r4pt0r\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Ewhat do you mean effects? like sound, a loud bang of some sort?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBasically, this\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BHBevPYVzaY\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BHBevPYVzaY\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd yep, if not done properly, it could end up buggy and unpleasant\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fleb","CreatedById":63851,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-03T20:20:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EKind of like this? \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/kp9CebbRZc8?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/56405-0-23-0-90-Atmospheric-Sound-Enhancement?highlight=pizzaoverhead\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/56405-0-23-0-90-Atmospheric-Sound-Enhancement?highlight=pizzaoverhead\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex","CreatedById":75164,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-04T01:44:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fleb\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Fleb\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EKind of like this? \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI thought of that mod the second I read the OP! I remembered watching that months ago \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-04T01:55:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022katateochi\u0022 data-cite=\u0022katateochi\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIn theory I\u0027d like this. It would need to be really nicely implemented though, it could end up being a rather buggy sound effect. ie what happens if you\u0027re flying just around the threshold for it, that may result in the sound constantly being played which would be rather unpleasant.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve actually had a plane stuck in the moment of going transonic ( under FAR, because it had just enough thrust set to get to that point ) - it was flying around with a visible shock cone for over an hour, I hate to think what canned booms would have done at that point \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/s8SJz6\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://farm8.staticflickr.com/7664/17154390247_b51c73cd89_z.jpg\u0022 alt=\u002217154390247_b51c73cd89_z.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-05-04T01:58:13Z\u0022 title=\u002205/04/2015 01:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EMay 4, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Van Disaster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aanker","CreatedById":70274,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-05-04T03:02:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWould make for a nice effect, perhaps to avoid the bugginess it would be triggered only if you have a certain acceleration across the sound barrier?\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}